sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant GW as KServe/Istio Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant GRPC as Caikit gRPC Server<br/>runtime.grpc.port/TCP
    participant HTTP as Caikit HTTP Server<br/>runtime.http.port/TCP
    participant Predict as GlobalPredictServicer
    participant Train as GlobalTrainServicer
    participant MM as ModelManager
    participant Module as Loaded Module
    participant MMesh as ModelMesh Controller
    participant MRSvc as ModelRuntimeServicer
    participant Loader as CoreModelLoader
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 1: Model Inference (gRPC)
    Client->>GW: Inference request
    GW->>GRPC: gRPC request<br/>TLS/mTLS/plaintext (configurable)
    GRPC->>Predict: Route to servicer
    Predict->>MM: Retrieve loaded model
    MM->>Module: Module.run()
    Module-->>MM: Prediction result
    MM-->>Predict: Result
    Predict-->>GRPC: gRPC response
    GRPC-->>GW: Response
    GW-->>Client: Inference result

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 2: Model Inference (HTTP with SSE streaming)
    Client->>GW: POST /{prefix}/task/{task_name}
    GW->>HTTP: HTTP/HTTPS request<br/>TLS/mTLS/plaintext (configurable)
    HTTP->>Predict: FastAPI handler → servicer
    Predict->>MM: Retrieve loaded model
    MM->>Module: Module.run() (streaming)
    Module-->>MM: Stream of results
    MM-->>Predict: Result stream
    Predict-->>HTTP: SSE event stream
    HTTP-->>GW: Server-Sent Events
    GW-->>Client: SSE streaming response

    Note over MMesh,S3: Flow 3: Model Loading (ModelMesh Sidecar)
    MMesh->>MRSvc: loadModel()<br/>Unix socket or gRPC/TCP
    MRSvc->>MM: load_model()
    MM->>Loader: CoreModelLoader
    Loader->>S3: Download model artifacts<br/>HTTPS/443, HMAC/IAM auth
    S3-->>Loader: Model artifacts
    Loader-->>MM: Model loaded in memory
    MM-->>MRSvc: Load success + model size
    MRSvc-->>MMesh: ModelResponse(sizeInBytes)

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 4: Model Training
    Client->>HTTP: POST /{prefix}/{train_rpc}<br/>Training request
    HTTP->>Train: FastAPI handler → servicer
    Train->>MM: train()
    MM->>Module: Module.train()<br/>(thread/subprocess)
    Module->>S3: Save trained model<br/>HTTPS/443
    S3-->>Module: Confirmation
    Module-->>MM: Training complete
    MM-->>Train: TrainingJob status
    Train-->>HTTP: Training ID + status
    HTTP-->>Client: 200 OK (training_id)
